Natural Language Requirements:  

1. Initialization Phase  
   - Set initial state to "No Error"  
   - Prepare a temporary structure to store conversion results  

2. Latitude Conversion Process  
   a. Numerical Calculation  
      - Seconds to decimal degrees: sec/3600  
      - Minutes to decimal degrees: min/60  
      - Sum degrees to form raw value  
   b. Direction Handling  
      - S (South) direction takes negative value  
      - N (North) direction remains positive  
      - Invalid direction marks an error  
   c. Validity Check  
      - Direction character must be N/S  
      - Total degrees absolute value ≤ 90°  
      - Minute/second values ≤ 59  

3. Longitude Conversion Process  
   a. Numerical Calculation  
      - Seconds to decimal degrees: sec/3600  
      - Minutes to decimal degrees: min/60  
      - Sum degrees to form raw value  
   b. Direction Handling  
      - W (West) direction takes negative value  
      - E (East) direction remains positive  
      - Invalid direction marks an error  
   c. Validity Check  
      - Direction character must be E/W  
      - Total degrees absolute value ≤ 180°  
      - Minute/second values ≤ 59  

4. Error Handling  
   - If any error occurs:  
     * Clear conversion results (set latitude/longitude to zero)  
     * Retain the last occurred error code  
   - If no errors:  
     * Preserve calculation results  
     * Mark success status  

5. Output Handling  
   - Error status indicated by bit15  
   - Ensure ENO remains always valid